The South African Investment Conference (SAIC) kicked off in Sandton, north of Johannesburg, on Thursday morning,  with a number of business entities making project announcements totaling over R200 billion. From a document released by SAIC, 49 entities are said to be involved in South African-related projects ranging from R20 Million to R42 Billion in value. The African Development Bank Group is cited as having investments or projects to the value of R42 Billion in total. Below is an infographic showing the 10 biggest commitments made at the 4th South African Investment Conference:  10 BIG INVESTMENTS Big business has taken heed of governments' call to invest in South Africa Renergen Implats  Anglo American Sedibelo African Rainbow Minerals African Development Bank Scatec Waterfall Ford Below are some of ﻿the companies that have pledged the biggest monetary investments New Development Bank R42 B R21.7 ﻿B R18 B R16.4 B R16 B R14 B R11.8 B R11 B R10 B R9.4 B *A total of 49 entities have been published in a document released by SA Investment Conference listing that the entities are involved in project announcements set to benefit the country. The top 10 investors are working on projects totalling R170.3 billion. SOURCE: South Africa Investment Conference announced at the SOUTH AFRICA INVESTMENT CONFERENCE (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));